  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Let us see if you have understood 'Queues' with an implementation problem.\n\nTaskWrite a program to print numbers in a specific pattern using a queue.\n\nThe pattern starts with 1 and alternates between printing one number and enqueueing the next number.\nThe pattern follows these rules:\n\n\nPrint 1.\nEnqueue 2.\nPrint 3.\nEnqueue 4.\nPrint 5.\nEnqueue 6.\nPrint 7.\n... and so on.\nOnce all numbers are completed - dequeue the remaining numbers\nCheck the sample output below for N=10N = 10N=10.\n\nUpdate the `NumberPattern` class in the IDE to solve this problem.",
    "constraints": [
      "1 ≤ T ≤ 10",
      "1 ≤ N ≤ 1000",
      "All numbers fit in 32‑bit signed integer"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "First line contains an integer T (1 ≤ T ≤ 10), the number of test cases. Each of the next T lines contains a single integer N (1 ≤ N ≤ 1000).",
    "outputFormat": "For each test case output a line with N space‑separated integers: first all odd numbers from 1 to N in increasing order, then all even numbers from 1 to N in increasing order.",
    "sampleTestCases": [
      {
        "id": "sample_1",
        "input": "1\n10",
        "output": "1 3 5 7 9 2 4 6 8 10",
        "explanation": "Odds up to 10 are printed first (1,3,5,7,9) then evens (2,4,6,8,10)."
      },
      {
        "id": "sample_2",
        "input": "2\n1\n5",
        "output": "1\n1 3 5 2 4",
        "explanation": "First test case N=1 prints only 1. Second test case N=5 prints odds 1 3 5 followed by evens 2 4."
      },
      {
        "id": "sample_3",
        "input": "1\n7",
        "output": "1 3 5 7 2 4 6",
        "explanation": "Odds up to 7 (1,3,5,7) then evens up to 7 (2,4,6)."
      }
    ]
  },
